etymologies: late 19th century: from stationary, on the pattern of rotor

definitions: the stationary portion of an electric generator or motor, especially of an induction motor.
shortDefinitions: stationary portion of electric generator or motor

definitions: a row of small stationary airfoils attached to the casing of an axial-flow turbine, positioned between the rotors.
shortDefinitions: row of small stationary aerofoils fixed to casing of axial-flow turbine, positioned between rotors
